Yuhao Min

Bio

Hello! I am Yuhao Min, a Ph.D.candidate at the Nilfer Ertekin-Taner Lab at Mayo Clinic. My research focus on understanding the complex molecular and cellular changes in neurodegenerative brains using systems biology tools, and translating the findings into therapeutic targets.

As an undergraduate student at University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign, I worked at the Huimin Zhao Lab to help develop better tools for synthetic biology applications.

Education

Mayo Clinic Graduate School of Biomedical Sciences

Jacksonville, FL | 2019 - Present

Ph.D.in Clinic and Translational Sciecnes

University of Illinois at Urbana-Chamaign

Urbana, IL | 2014 - 2019

B.S. in Chemistry | B.S. in Molecular and Cellular Biology | Minor in Computer Science

Experience

Nilfer Ertekin-Taner Lab | 2020 - Present

Undergraduate Research Assistant

Huimin Zhao Lab | 2015 - 2018
